One refreshing thing about Cuban tobacco products is there is no English anywhere on the cigarillo packs. Only Spanish and Bulgarian writing. Effective multipolarity.

Listening to a bunch of British guys playing volleyball and genuinely in awe at their accents, they talk like side characters in a Pirates of The Caribbean movie. I genuinely thought they were joking at first but they actually talk like "bloody lovely, lads", "you bloody cheats!"

It's genuinely the thickest English accent I have ever heard, like how I would uneducatedly imagine British East India Company employees would talk to each other on a ship. I just hear the words "mate", "bloody", "cheeky" sounding off repeatedly. I love the English people.
